    • Constructor Detail

      • BagSelectionSemiSupervised

        public BagSelectionSemiSupervised(int nbrows,
                                  int labeledNo,
                                  int unlabeledNo,
                                  ClusRandomNonstatic rnd)
        Creates a new bag selection from dataset consisting of labeled and unlabeled examples. Labeled and unlabeled examples are sampled separately to avoid having only unlabeled examples in a bag. Dataset is assumed to be sorted so that the labeled examples come first, while unlabeled second.
        Parameters:
        nbrows - the total number of instances
        labeledStart - starting position of labeled examples (usually 0)
        labeledNo - the number of labeled examples to be sampled
        unlabeledstart - starting position of unlabeled examples in dataset
        unlabeledNo - the number of unlabeled examples to be sampled
